                    <ns0:physDesc>
                        <ns0:objectDesc>
                            <ns0:supportDesc>
                                <ns0:support><ns0:p>Large slab of grey/brown stone. Forms a pair with <ns0:ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001159">ISic001159</ns0:ref>, as they are similar in size, material, and the form and shape of the letters. All sides are almost square, but for the chip on right edge at the end of line 2. The back is almost flat. Traces of modern mortar on side.</ns0:p>
                                    <ns0:material ana="#material.stone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html">stone (grey)</ns0:material>
                                    <ns0:dimensions>
                                        <ns0:height unit="cm">23</ns0:height>
                                        <ns0:width unit="cm">32</ns0:width>
                                        <ns0:depth unit="cm">9</ns0:depth>
                                    </ns0:dimensions>
                                </ns0:support>
                                <ns0:condition />
		    </ns0:supportDesc>
                            <ns0:layoutDesc>
                                <ns0:layout><ns0:p>Three lines of Greek text not centred on stone. Line 2 is shifted significantly to right, in comparison with lines 1 and 3. Guidelines are the top and bottom of each line are still evident, but less pronounced than on <ns0:ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001159">ISic001159</ns0:ref></ns0:p>
                                    <ns0:rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</ns0:rs>
                                	<ns0:damage />
			</ns0:layout>
                            </ns0:layoutDesc>
                        </ns0:objectDesc>
                        <ns0:handDesc>
                            <ns0:handNote><ns0:p>Letters are extremely regular and neat, with letter heights all identical. Letters are thin, tall and evenly spaced. Terminal dots carved on all letters. Use of the classic zeta in line 1.</ns0:p>
                                <ns0:locus from="line1" to="line3">Lines 1-3</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" atLeast="40" atMost="40">40</ns0:height>
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                                <ns0:locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</ns0:locus>
                                <ns0:dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <ns0:height unit="mm" />
                                </ns0:dimensions>
                            </ns0:handNote>
                        </ns0:handDesc>
