            <ns0:div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <ns0:p>Zopyros, son or Artemon, is likely the same man who is either the husband or father of the Phaino in <ns0:ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001159">ISic001159</ns0:ref>. Oikidia is a unicum, and its meaning is uncertain. here are half a dozen other mentions of the name Zopyros in Sicily and it is quite common elsewhere, Artemon is equally common both in Sicily and elsewhere.</ns0:p>
            </ns0:div>
